title: WATCH: Taylor's still got it
text:
Phil Taylor throws a 142 finish   Nottingham Power pummels a magical checkout in the Premier League on Thursday night By Sky Sports Darts Last Updated: 09/02/17 11:53pm The moment of week two is Phil Taylor's 142 checkout Phil Taylor proved that he still has the power on the oche as he stole the show in Nottingham with a magnificent 142 checkout against James Wade. 
Taylor and Wade battled out an entertaining draw in a game which featured four ton-plus finishes and a quartet of 180s from the 2009 champion as both players remained unbeaten. 
An early 121 finish from Wade moved him into a 2-0 lead before Taylor matched the checkout to respond and then took out 104 to level at three-all.   
Wade followed two maximums with tops finishes as he led 4-3 and 5-4, only for Taylor to level in leg 10 with double 19 and then fire in a sensational 142 combination to lead 6-5. 
Wade, though, would not be denied as he took out 56 on tops in the decider to claim his share of the points. 
Following close behind was Michael van Gerwen as the brilliant Dutchman struck a stunning 170 checkout in the fourth leg of his win against Peter Wright. MVG struck this 170 finish on his way to victory 
Click on the video at the top of the page to see Taylor nail his finish and then watch MVG's monster outshot.
